    <abstract>
      <t>This document defines generic constructions for hybrid Key Encapsulation Mechanisms (KEMs) based on combining a post-quantum (PQ) KEM with a traditional cryptographic component. Hybrid KEMs built using these constructions provide strong security properties as long as either of the underlying algorithms are secure.</t>
